        "title": "How to handle array out of bound exception",
        "body": "<p>I am writing function that getting 2 strings.\nevery string represents version of something.<\/p>\n\n<p>For example:<\/p>\n\n<p>String var1 = \"1.1.1\";<\/p>\n\n<p>String var2 = \"1.1.2\";<\/p>\n\n<p>and returns which string is a newer version.<\/p>\n\n<p>My code :<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>   public  void main(String var1, String var2) {\n\n    String[] arrayA = var1.split(\"\\\\.\");\n\n    String[] arrayB = var2.split(\"\\\\.\");\n\n    for (int i = 0; i &lt; arrayA.length; i++) {\n\n            Integer number1 = Integer.parseInt(arrayA[i]);\n\n            Integer number2 = Integer.parseInt(arrayB[i]);\n\n            if (number1.equals(number2)) {\n\n                textView.setText(\"arrays equal\");\n\n            } else if (number1 &gt; number2) {\n\n                textView.setText(\"array A newer version\");\n\n                break;\n\n            } else if (number2 &gt; number1) {\n\n                textView.setText(\"array B newer version\");\n\n                break;\n            }  \n    }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Until now everything works fine.<\/p>\n\n<p>My problem starts when the arrays have different length<\/p>\n\n<p>( I always camper  shorterArray to longerArray )<\/p>\n\n<p>if i camper var1 = \"2.3\"; to  var2=\"3.3.3\";  i getting the right answer.<\/p>\n\n<p>but if i camper var1 = \"2.3\"; to var2 = \"2.3.1\"; <\/p>\n\n<p>i always get \"equal\".<\/p>\n\n<p>Any suggestions how to deal with it?<\/p>\n",
